This test will check that exo helper opens applications correctly 
Ensure you have more than one browser installed (1)
Ensure you have more than one mail reader installed (2)
Ensure more than one file manager is installed (3)
<dl>
    <dt>Open Settings -> Preferred Applications</dt>
        <dd>Preferred Applications opens at Internet</dd>
    <dt>Select Web default web browser</dt>
		<dd>[FILL VERIFICATION]</dd>
	
	<dt>Drop down appears</dt>
		<dd>[FILL VERIFICATION]</dd>
    <dt>select a different one (1)</dt>
	<dd>Browser name changes if choice amended</dd>
    <dt>Press Help</dt>
	<dd>Online help opens in browser</dd>
    <dt>change default in Mail reader dropdown (2)</dt>
    <dt>Open a terminal and type <code>exo-open mailto:xfce4-dev@xfce.org</code> and press enter</dt>
	<dd>Correct mail reader opens with correct e-mail address in To field of a new e-mail</dd>
    <dt>Select Utilities tab</dt>
	<dd>File Manager and Terminal Emulator appear</dd>
    <dt>change default file manager (3)</dt>
	<dd>File Manager changes if choice amended</dd>
    <dt>Open a terminal and type <code>exo-open --launch FileManager</code> and press enter</dt>
	<dd>File Manager selected in drop down opens</dd>
    <dt>Select Terminal Emulator</dt>
	<dd>Drop down appears</dd>
    <dt>Select X Terminal</dt>
		<dd>[FILL VERIFICATION]</dd>
    <dt>Press Super+T</dt>
	<dd>Selected terminal opens</dd>
</dl>
[False Condition] 
